<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Thermo Fisher (TMO)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc. — using recent actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })} · Data: Latest Financials</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  {intrinsicValuePerShare !== null ? (
    <>
      <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
      <div class="verdict-card">
        <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
        <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
        <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${fetchedPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
        <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
          {verdictText}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
      <div class="stats-row">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(getRecentValue(incData['Revenue']) / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">LTM Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(latestFCF / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${getRecentValue(incData['EPS (Diluted)'])?.toFixed(2) || 'N/A'}</div>
          <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">{getRecentValue(incData['Operating Margin'])?.toFixed(1) || 'N/A'}%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Net Cash (Debt)</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
      <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
      <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
          <p>Thermo Fisher generated <strong>${(fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(2)} billion</strong> in free cash flow recently. This is operating cash flow minus capital expenditures. It represents the actual cash available to distribute to shareholders or reinvest for growth.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
          <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This assumes normalization in the life sciences tools market after pandemic highs and subsequent destocking, alongside structural growth in biopharma spending.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
          <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong>. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>. This captures all value from Year 6 to infinity, reflecting a mature but essential medical tools provider.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
          <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong> — our required rate of return. This cost of equity accounts for a stable, low-beta healthcare compounder, grounded by a 4.18% 10Y Treasury baseline plus equity risk premium.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">5</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
          <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(2)}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
      <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
      <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

      <div class="assumption-grid">
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
          <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
            Following post-COVID inventory destocking and bioprocessing headwinds, Thermo Fisher's fundamental growth profile in analytical instruments, diagnostics, and lab products remains intact. We model a conservative 8% recovery and growth phase.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
          <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
            10Y Treasury: 4.18%. With a lower beta typical of mega-cap healthcare and life sciences, an 8% discount rate reflects the lower risk profile and steady, recurring revenue nature of TMO's business model.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
          <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
            A 3% perpetual growth rate aligns with long-term global healthcare spending growth, inflation, and nominal GDP. It acknowledges TMO's entrenched position as the "Amazon of Science" providing mission-critical lab supplies globally.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
      <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
              <th>FCF ($M)</th>
              <th>PV Factor</th>
              <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Base (Current)</td>
              <td>${Math.round(fcfBase).toLocaleString()}</td>
              <td>—</td>
              <td>—</td>
            </tr>
            {projectedFCF.map(p => (
              <tr>
                <td>Year {p.year}</td>
                <td>${Math.round(p.fcf).toLocaleString()}</td>
                <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
                <td>${Math.round(p.pvFCF).toLocaleString()}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
            <tr class="row-total">
              <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
              <td class="highlight-cell">${Math.round(pvPhase1).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
      <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
              <th>Value ($M)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × {(1 + growthRateTerminal).toFixed(3)})</td>
              <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Terminal Value (FCF₆ ÷ ({(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% − {(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%))</td>
              <td>${Math.round(terminalValue).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="row-total">
              <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
              <td class="highlight-cell">${Math.round(pvTerminalValue).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
      <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
              <th>Value ($M)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
              <td>${Math.round(pvPhase1).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
              <td>${Math.round(pvTerminalValue).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
              <td>${Math.round(enterpriseValue).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
              <td>${Math.round(netCash).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>= Equity Value</td>
              <td>${Math.round(equityValue).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
              <td>{Math.round(sharesOutstanding).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="row-total">
              <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
              <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

