      <!-- ═══ SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS ═══ -->
      <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
      <p>Our base case uses {(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% growth and {(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% discount rate. Here's what the intrinsic value looks like under different assumptions.</p>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="sensitivity-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
              {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
                <th class={Math.abs(g - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(0)}%</th>
              ))}
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
              <tr>
                <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(0)}%</td>
                {row.values.map((v, i) => (
                  <td class={Math.abs(row.dr - discountRate) < 0.001 && Math.abs(sensitivityGrowth[i] - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>
                    {v !== null ? '$' + v : 'N/A'}
                  </td>
                ))}
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
      <h2>What This Model Doesn't Capture</h2>

      <h3>Upside risks (our number could be too low)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Biopharma recovery:</strong> A faster-than-expected rebound in biotech funding and bioprocessing demand could drive double-digit growth.</li>
        <li><strong>Accretive M&A:</strong> TMO is a serial acquirer. Highly accretive acquisitions funded by debt or cash could boost FCF per share beyond our organic projections.</li>
        <li><strong>Margin expansion:</strong> Efficiency initiatives (PPI Business System) could drive operating margins permanently higher.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Downside risks (our number could be too high)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Prolonged destocking:</strong> If the post-pandemic inventory glut persists longer than anticipated in the life sciences sector.</li>
        <li><strong>Macroeconomic weakness:</strong> Reduced academic or government funding globally for scientific research and healthcare.</li>
        <li><strong>Debt load:</strong> High interest rates on their substantial debt load ($30B+) could compress net margins and available free cash flow.</li>
      </ul>

